# Workshop : React random quote

## Overview 
    This workshop is dedicated to the wildcodeschool student to learn and practice reactJS

## Installation

### 1. Clone or download this repository : 
```
git clone git@github.com:Brian-boudrioux/workshop-react-randomQuote.git
cd workshop-react-randomQuote
```

### 2. Install the dependencies.

```
npm install
```

## Starting the Project - Dev Mode

Run the following command: `npm run dev`.

## Steps : 
URL de l'API : [Quotes api](https://type.fit/api/quotes)

Rendu final : ![alt maquette quote generator](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

-  In your `App` component : Declare a `quotes` state with a empty array as default value and a `selectedQuote` state with null as default value

- In your `App` component : Use the `useEffect` hook to fetch the quotes API and set your `quotes` state with the returned data and your `selectedQuote` state with the first element of the returned data

- Create a `Quote` component who takes two props : `({text, author})` and displays the data from the props as presented in the model above

- Import and call your `Quote` component into your `App` component and pass to it the text and author props using the data stored into your `selectedQuote` state

- In your `App` component : Create a `getRandomQuote` function who will return a random element from the data stored in the `quotes` state

- In Your `Quote` component : Add a button "New quote" which when clicked will update the `selectedQuote` state using the data returned by the `getRandomQuote` function

Good luck !
